Ugh! It's so annoying that I even have to do that. Well, with that said ...


Obama was NOT an amazing president. He was an amazing celebrity. There's a difference and it's pretty important. When we're talking about Obama, we're talking about a guy who received a Nobel Peace Prize, then turned around and dropped more bombs on the world than any other president in history. We're talking about a guy who campaigned on the promise that he wouldn't have any lobbyists in his administration, then turned around and WROTE HIMSELF WAIVERS so that he could hire DOZENS of them! He even promised to leave retailers in legal states alone, then turned around and raided legal retailers!


And THIS is the guy you are saying is "an amazing president"?!?!?!


Again, I'm not a fan of Trump. I didn't vote for him and I'm not going to vote for him next time. That said ...


Trump passed meaningful criminal justice reform, something Obama SHOULD HAVE prioritized as our first black president.
Obama passed hundreds of thousands of pages of needless regulations that crippled our economy for the entire 8 years of his presidency, which forced record numbers of minorities onto the welfare rolls, and he called that an "accomplishment".
As soon as Trump took office, he repealed much of the Obama regulations, the economy boomed, and minority unemployment fell to an all-time low! All those people Obama put on welfare started coming off ... and you guys think OBAMA was the superior president?! Seriously?!?!?!?!


Trump has done FAR MORE to help minorities, especially blacks, but somehow he's the racist?! Seriously?! Look, I'm a minority ... and if that's racism, I'll take it! Yes, please!
